I have the following expression that is giving error.
```javascript
const monacoConfig: NgxMonacoEditorConfig = {
    onMonacoLoad: () => {
        (window as any).monaco = (window as any).monaco || null;
    }
};
```
he is returning this error

```
ERROR in Error during template compile of 'VimboEditorCodeModule'
  Function expressions are not supported in decorators in '…µ0'
    '…µ0' contains the error at src/@vimbo/components/editor-code/editor-code.module.ts(16,19)
      Consider changing the function expression into an exported function.
```

how could i change the expression using the hint informed in the terminal.
remembering that, I care about it as follows.

```
